SIMPLE: heliograph
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heliograph
<hw>He"li*o*graph</hw> <pr>(h⟦emac⟧"l⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧*gr⟦adot⟧f)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Helio-</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A picture taken by heliography; a
photograph.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for taking photographs of the
sun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An apparatus for telegraphing by means of the sun's
rays. See <er>Heliotrope</er>, 3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heliograph</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Heliograph
<hw>He"li*o*graph</hw> <pr>(h⟦emac⟧"l⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧*gr⟦adot⟧f)</pr>,
<pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To telegraph, or signal, with a
heliograph.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To photograph by sunlight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heliographic</ent>⟦br⟧
